channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: What the Heck?! RFK Jr. Tells Bizarre Story About Leaving a Dead Bear in Central Park
Mark Kelly posts cryptic message amid Kamala Harris veepstakes speculation
item.description: Sen. Mark Kelly of Arizona is one of the top contenders to be a running mate for Kamala Harris. Kelly posted a message on X Sunday that caused people to speculate that he was picked.

item.title: Sen. Mullin: 'Snake' Iran Needs Its Head Cut Off
item.description: Iran should finally be held accountable for its longtime sponsorship of terror across the globe, Sen. Markwayne Mullin, R-Okla., said Sunday.

item.title: Here We Go Again: Students Prepping for Even More Pro-Hamas Campus Protests This Fall
RFK Jr. admits to dumping dead bear cub in Central Park as Roseanne Barr listens in bizarre video
item.description: Presidential candidate Robert F. Kennedy, Jr. made a bizarre admission on Sunday. He said he left a dead bear cub in NYC's Central Park in 2014 after his plan to skin it didn't work out.

item.title: Carville: Kamala Should Conditionally Accept Debate
item.description: Democrat strategist James Carville suggested Saturday that Vice President Kamala Harris should accept a Fox News invitation to debate former President Donald Trump next month, but with one caveat.

item.title: Sen. Tim Scott Marries Mindy Noce, Continuing His Inspirational Story of Hope and the American Dream
Biden approves Florida emergency declaration over Tropical Storm Debby
item.description: President Biden has approved an emergency declaration for Florida in anticipation of Tropical Storm Debby, the White House confirmed Sunday.

item.title: Musk-Backed PAC Under Investigation in Michigan
item.description: A political action committee backed by billionaire Elon Musk is under investigation in Michigan for possible violations of state laws, a spokesperson for the Michigan secretary of state's office said in a statement on Sunday.

item.title: Hilarious Post by Dems' Account Raises Questions About Who They Really Want As Nominee
John Kirby dodges grilling over plea agreement for 9/11 terrorists: ‘Didn’t hear an answer’
item.description: White House National Security Council communications adviser John Kirby dodged answering Fox News' Jacqui Heinrich's questions over a rescinded plea deal to three 9/11 terrorists.

item.title: Blinken: Iran Could Attack Israel in 24 Hours
item.description: Secretary of State Antony Blinken said an attack by Iran and Hezbollah could happen as early as Monday, reported Axios, citing three sources briefed on a call Blinken had with G7 leaders late Sunday.

item.title: Carville Offers Kamala Advice on Fox Debate With Trump. Be Careful What You Wish For, James.
Kamala Harris faces crucial week ahead in 2024 presidential showdown with Donald Trump
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris faces a consequential week ahead on the campaign trail, starting with her crucial decision on a running mate, as she faces off against Donald Trump in the 2024 election

item.title: Congress Leaves DC, Fails to Pass VA Budget Request
item.description: Congress failed to pass legislation addressing a nearly $3 billion budget shortfall for the Department of Veterans Affairs before leaving town, leaving millions of veterans at risk.
